The most ✨ELITE✨ @mionettoproseccousa mimosas 🥂

@mionettoproseccousa Organic Prosecco Strawberry Basil Mimosas - YUM. Recipe below 👇🏼 

These are SO GOOD. Make sure to tag us if you try them!!! 

RECIPE:
10 Large Strawberries 🍓 
1 Large Bunch of Basil 🌱
3 TBSP Raw Honey
1/2 Cup Water
@mionettoproseccousa Organic Prosecco (literally the best Prosecco on earth)

➡️ Blend strawberries, basil, honey, & water for 90 seconds (yes, 90 seconds - it becomes thick & delish).

➡️STRAIN strawberry mixture! Seriously - don’t skip this step. It gets all the strawberry seeds out & makes the mixture SO smooth! 

➡️ Add 2/3 TBSP of your strawberry/basil mixture to a glass & top with @mionettoproseccousa organic Prosecco! 

🥂CHEERS

2024 - READY FOR YOU QUEEN 👑
Sourdough 🍞

A few months ago a sweet friend left this journal on my desk. I’ve been hanging onto it SPECIFICALLY for this day. ✨

I thought 2023 was MY year. It had its ups & downs for sure (that’s life) but I learned SO much. I healed SO much. I grew SO much. 

I really pulled back from social media last year because honestly I didn’t know what to say or WHO I was here on social media anymore (ironic that I own and operate a creative agency and don’t even do my own socials, right?) I needed to realign; reset. I needed to find my voice again. I feel ready to re-introduce myself and start sharing the content/messaging I really want to share with all of you.

For YEARS I’ve worked & worked & worked & worked and constantly pour into other people (that 99% of the time don’t pour back into me). Don’t get me wrong, I LOVE working - but I have always personally DIRECTLY tied my value as a person to my performance in my career. Working has always been my identity. 

I’m more than just my “job”. I always have been - I just don’t think I’ve ever said that out loud until now. I’m tired of feeling like a machine. I love writing, cooking, art, & singing. And I’m actually really good at those things. I love connecting people, and having genuine conversations. I love talking about spirituality, mindset, and abundance. I love sharing the things I’ve learned with others so they, too, can experience the complete and total mindset transformation that I have.

In 2024 I’m not setting any goals. Rather - I’m committing in FULL FORCE to 3 things…

ABUNDANCE - ADVENTURE - ALIGNMENT

If any person, place, thing, or experience does not offer me one of those things - simply, I’m out. 

So here we are - a new year. Im ready for all the love, joy, happiness, excitement, tears, pain, learning, growing, & transformation I know 2024 will bring. 

❤️Katie
